summary: Had a dream I found a spell to bring my mother back to life, but she didn't get along with my step mother at all, I was...
body: Had a dream I found a spell to bring my mother back to life, but she didn’t get along with my step mother at all, I was screaming at my step mother that my mother will be here long after she is gone, because she called her a over dramatic brat for getting upset over my step mother changing things in the house, specifically where the dragon statues were, which is weird because my house never had any of these statues, my father asked if my mother got upset while watching game if thrones and seeing bran run with the dragons(which doesn’t happen), after my mother left we went out to look for her and didn’t find her, saw another mother find her daughter in what looked like a NYC square on Christmas, get back home to find out she left my brother outside by himself (he was a little kid again) in the cold with no coat on, which made me furious, so at that point I was thinking this is not my mother and I need to get rid of her

blog.name: honesttoblogmoviereviews
blog.title: I Know Nothing Jon Snow
blog.description: I used to be a movie review blog but I just finished Game of Thrones so whattup bastards? (Btw as an aspiring film major I’m coming at this from ONLY the television show NOT at all the books!)

body:
Bronn

So here’s the reason why Bronn is my favorite and literally should be everyone’s favorite character. For starters he starts off as just ol regular sellsword like cool there’s plenty. But, he stands out because of his strange loyalty and unmatched wit. He is the only one that constantly stood by Tyrion (yes paid but you can see the friendship which also made me question why he wouldn’t leave but you gotta chase that coin) aside from his trial. He is the only character that knows his worth, what he is and isn’t entitled to, and when to back out of a damn situation—aside from stupidly saving Jaime. He helped Jaime become less pathetic while also battling like a superhero. Really he is one of the only swordsmen that lives up to his reputation. My only complaint is that he didn’t go save his sand snake from Cersei because that was bad character development. However, overall he is a great character because of his comedy, sass, swordsmanship, friendship, loyalty, aggressiveness, assertiveness, persistence, and greed.

title: Fandom tag game II
body:
RULES: Choose any three fandoms (in random order) and answer the questions, then tag 10 people you want to know better.

Tagged by: @imaginarydragonling because apparently she hates me <3

Three fandoms:

  • Boku no Hero Academia
  • Game of Thrones
  • Haikyuu

The first character you loved:

  • Midoriya
  • Arya Stark
  • Hinata

The character you never expected to love so much:

  • Momo Yaoyorozu
  • Sansa Stark
  • Asahi

The character you relate to the most:

  • Aizawa
  • Cersei Lannister
  • Ryuu Tanaka

As for me, I would choose:

  • Ochako
  • Asha/Yara Greyjoy (As if there weren’t enough names to keep track of, you had to go rename a character for the show?)
  • Suga-senpaiii <3

The character you would slap:

  • Mineta, though I bet he’d enjoy it, little perv
  • Jeoffrey
  • Lev

Three favourite characters:

  • Deku, Ocacho, Kacchan
  • Tyrion,  Sandor, Margaery 
  • Tetsuro Kuroo, Nishinoya, Oikawa

Three OTPs:

  • Bakudeku, Ochako x Bakugou, Ochako x Tsu-chan
  • Daisuga, Kuroken, Iwaoi
  • SanSan, Sansa x Margaery, Arya x Gendry

I tag @houseofgeeks @scribeoffate @iguanastevens @scottishearthbender @iluvnutella007
